data.description: Gorgeous 19th century Chester County farmhouse bursting with charm and character inside, and with an equally magical outdoor setting.  You will fall in love with this home and property.  Characteristic details include a covered front porch complete with a porch swing, spiral staircases, original exposed stone walls and beams, wide-plank hickory hardwood floors, arched doorways, surprising nooks, and flexible indoor and outdoor spaces to utilize however you feel most inspired.  All of this, perched on a truly breathtaking and private 1.2 acres of land with outbuildings.  The main level hosts an impressive 2-story foyer, charming kitchen, original stone dining room with reading nook and built-ins, a gorgeous large family room with vaulted ceiling and wood-burning fireplace, a gym (or home office space), and the primary bedroom with a full, updated bath, skylight, woodstove, walk-in-closet and its own private brick patio!  From the main living space, step outside to the deck and patio to grill, dine, relax, and entertain with a stunning natural setting.  Back inside on the second level, you will find two additional bedrooms, a den (or bedroom space) with original floors, and another full, updated bathroom.  The third level offers another bedroom and large storage space, with original floors and charming exposed stone walls. Bonus features of this home include an over-sized, detached 3-car garage with a spacious, completely finished second floor with central air giving endless possibilities as a game room, studio, office, gym, guest space, or whatever your needs require.  The fully-fenced property, lush with mature landscaping and backyard view of a horse pasture, also includes a shaded deck, chicken coop, a large picturesque board-and-batten outbuilding wired with electricity that could be used as a workshop or she-shed, a separate studio, and so much more. Recent upgrades to the home include new water filtration system, basement radon extraction system, new washer, dishwasher and upgraded LED bulbs, hardware and fixtures.  Ideally located close to major roadways for commuting and close to everything this area has to offer, including Applecross golf course.  The current owner has traced the deed records back to 1880 and is happy to share the research with the next owner who can continue to trace the intriguing lineage of the home and land. Available only due to relocation and Sellers are including a 1 Year Cinch Home Warranty for Buyer at settlement .  Sellers are MOTIVATED. Be sure to view the 3D floorplans and video tour, and schedule your showing today!
